Robert Epstein




Robert D. Epstein
Mr. Epstein is one of the founders of Epstein, Cohen, Seif & Flora. He has practiced law since 1970, and was a partner with Epstein & Frisch for over 30 years.
LITIGATION
Mr. Epstein has engaged in many areas of civil litigation, including product liability, medical malpractice, automobile accidents, and complex business litigation.
Mr. Epstein was the first lawyer in the U.S. to litigate the constitutionality of a state’s ban on interstate shipments of wine. The resulting opinion by the U.S. Supreme Court in Granholm v. Heald found bans in Michigan and New York unconstitutional, opening the door for the interstate shipping of wine.
Mr. Epstein has handled over 20 similar suits in federal court.
MERGERS AND ACQUISITIONS
Mr. Epstein has handled over 500 business transactions involving the sale or purchase of a business. He has also lectured on the finer points of buying or selling a business, including assets, trade names, goodwill, and other related concerns.
IMMIGRATION
Mr. Epstein has handled most types of immigration issues for over 30 years, including family and work-based visa applications, asylum, and deportation cases, including appeals.
BUSINESS LAW
Mr. Epstein has worked with companies small and large on issues including lending, leasing, and formation of business entities.
